@flexiarg coordination/assignment-binding
@title Assignment Binding (G4)
@keywords assignment, exclusive, conflict, concurrency
@audience coordination maintainers, futon3b builders
@tone formal-analytic
@references [futon-theory/proof-path futon-theory/stop-the-line]
@theory-grounding [A2(Attributable) A1(Auditability)]

! conclusion:
  If you want replayable proof-paths, record an explicit assignment evidence record that binds agent-id to task-id and treat conflicting assignments as a gate rejection.

  + context: Coordination needs a durable "who is responsible" record.
  + IF:
    you want artifacts and validation outcomes to be attributable

  + HOWEVER:
    without a recorded assignment, later evidence cannot be traced to accountable actors

  + THEN:
    emit an Assignment record at G4 and reject when a task is already assigned to another agent (exclusive binding)

  + BECAUSE:
    attribution is a core coordination invariant; ambiguity becomes debt

